comments.body:
@bmoore-msft is the AzureRM Module using the ADAL for authenticating (browser popup to log in)? if so there is a possibility this part of an known issue with WinForms and ISE. https://windowsserver.uservoice.com/forums/301869-powershell/suggestions/11733891-powershell-ise-crashes-after-loading-winforms it presents itself as freezes or high CPU usage.

I can say from experience, that ISE has some quirks when you try to use it as a shall instead of as an IDE. I would recommend switching to a regular PS console if you are not doing development work.

In any event, this repo is for PowerShell Core (6.0.0) issues. Windows PowerShell 5.1 issues should be logged on [UserVoice](https://windowsserver.uservoice.com/forums/301869-powershell).
